Justice.

'The complaint had merit, serious laws were potentially broken.'

Michael
 McCrum, the San Antonio-based special prosecutor, said he 'took into 
account the fact that we're talking about a governor of a state – and a 
governor of the state of Texas, which we all love.'

'Obviously that carries a lot of importance,' McCrum said. 'But when it gets down to it, the law is the law.'

McCrum
